Eskom will suspend loadshedding so that the country can mourn the passing of His Majesty King Goodwill Zwelithini. In a statement released on Wednesday evening, the power utility said it will suspend load shedding between 10:00 and 14:00. Eskom said this was done to allow South Africans to witness the official memorial service which will take place at the KwaKhethomthandayo Royal Palace in Nongoma on Thursday, starting at 10 am. "This extraordinary measure has been implemented to allow the nation to witness a key and significant historical event at this difficult time in the life of the Zulu nation. "Afterwards, load-shedding will then be implemented and continue as previously communicated,‚Äù the statement read.